ZH: 他是一位著名的布道者。
EN: He is a well-known preacher.

ZH: 明天我会去布道。
EN: I will go preaching tomorrow.

ZH: 每周日他都会布道。
EN: He preaches every Sunday.

ZH: 布道是他的职业。
EN: Preaching is his profession.

ZH: 他的布道使人们受益匪浅。
EN: His preaching benefits people greatly.

ZH: 每次布道他都充满激情。
EN: He is always passionate when preaching.

ZH: 在教堂里，他经常布道。
EN: He often preaches in the church.

ZH: 布道活动将于下周开始。
EN: The preaching event will start next week.

ZH: 听他布道的人很多。
EN: Many people listen to his preaching.

ZH: 布道使人们找到了内心的平静。
EN: Preaching helps people find inner peace.

ZH: 她的布道使人心生敬畏。
EN: Her preaching inspires awe in people's hearts.

ZH: 布道是他传播福音的方式之一。
EN: Preaching is one of his ways to spread the gospel.

ZH: 我们要尊重每个人的布道观点。
EN: We should respect everyone's preaching views.

ZH: 这位牧师的布道风格很独特。
EN: The pastor has a unique preaching style.

ZH: 布道可以启发人们思考人生的意义。
EN: Preaching can inspire people to reflect on the meaning of life.

ZH: 他的布道内容充满希望和鼓励。
EN: His preaching is filled with hope and encouragement.

ZH: 布道的目的是帮助人们修正错误思维。
EN: The purpose of preaching is to help people correct wrong thinking.

ZH: 布道者们经常在社区做福音传播工作。
EN: Preachers often do evangelism work in the community.

ZH: 她非常专注地听着布道者的讲话。
EN: She listens attentively to the preacher's sermon.

ZH: 布道者用生动的语言吸引了许多信徒。
EN: The preacher attracts many believers with vivid language in their sermons.
